Motivation and Background¶

Give an overview of the project, motivation, background and goals.

Gaming as an industry has been growing over the years and has certainly grown exponentially at the height of the pandemic, with games like "Animal Crossing: New Horizons" and "Among Us" booming in popularity. Hence, I would like to study the overall amount of players it brought to the gaming industry.

Summary of Research Questions & Results¶

Repeat your research questions in a numbered list. After each research question, clearly state the answer/conclusion you determined. Do not give details or justifications yet — just the answer

1. How has gaming growth changed during to the pandemic?¶

Throughout the pandemic, people have been stuck at homes. I would like to find out whether the pandemic has had an impact on the gaming industry in general.

  • Yes, gaming has definitely grown over the pandemic. With a spike increase during 2020 that continues to the current day

2. Does the number of COVID-19 measures implemented correlate with the player count of various games?¶

By comparing the number of COVID-19 measures implemented around the world to the sum player count of online games, I will be able to observe their potential relationship.

  • There seems to be corrolation between COVID-19 measures and player count of online games, however with online games first increasing before COVID-19 measures.

3. How does the growth vary between genres of games during the pandemic?¶

Different games address different needs of individuals. Hence the pandemic may have impacted certain types of games more than others. By comparing the player count of different game genres, I can identify what people were looking for during the pandemic, whether it’s a social experience from a multiplayer game, the desire for competitiveness in strategy games, or solitary experiences from a singleplayer game.

  • Genres which provide an alternate reality for people to live in, like Adventure, RPG etc, relaxing games or competitive games grew tremendously during the pandemic. Surprisingly, massively multiplayer games did not rise significantly during the pandemic

4. How has free-to-play games been impacted differently from paid games during the pandemic?¶

Free-to-play have always appealed to a larger audience, due to its easy accessibility. Comparing them with paid games could help us understand whether people are more willing to spend money on video games during the pandemic. I will also compare games with different price ranges to find out how much people are willing to spend on video games during the periods which they seldom venture outside.

  • Indeed, free games player count has increased during the pandemic. Paid games did also increase, with more expensive games increasing later in the time.

Numbered list of dataset (with downloadable links) and a brief but clear description of each dataset used. Draw reference to the numbering when describing (data cleaning and analysis).

  3. https://steamcharts.com This website was webscrabbed in order to get the monthly average concurrent players.

Methodology

You should demonstrate the data science life cycle here (from data acquisition to cleaning to EDA and analysis etc).

1. How has gaming growth changed due to the pandemic?¶

First, I will calculate the sum player count of the online games per day. Afterwards, I will plot graphs against time of player count from 2017-2020, to observe the trend of the player count and find out whether there was a growth during 2020, the year of the pandemic.

2. Does the number of COVID-19 measures correlate with the player count of various games?¶

I will compare the sum of player count of the various games to the COVID-19 measures around the world by plotting a correlation graph. This would allow me to find the relationship with COVID-19 measures implemented against the number of people playing video games.

3. How does the growth vary between genres of games during the pandemic?¶

First, I will collate all the games into various categories using their genre on Steam. For example, multiplayer, singleplayer, RPG (Roleplaying Games), Sandbox etc. I will plot a boxplot of the average player count of each game genre to see the distribution of games with players across each genre, and plot a line graph to see the trend of each genre

4. How has free-to-play games been impacted differently from paid games during the pandemic?¶

First, I will collate all the games into different categories; free-to-play, \$0.01-\\$4.99, \$5.00-\\$9.99, \$10.00-\\$19.99, \$20.00-\\$39.99, \$39.99-\\$59.99, >=\$60. I will plot a boxplot of the average player count of each price range to see the distribution of games with players across each price range, and plot a line graph to see the trend of each price range

Q2: I shall get the total number of cumulative measures per date, any measure that is a phase out measure is considered as a "negative measure"

In [17]:
cummeasure=measures.iloc[:,[3,5]].copy()
cummeasure.iloc[:,1] = pd.to_datetime(cummeasure.DATE_IMPLEMENTED)
cummeasure["Value"]=cummeasure.LOG_TYPE.str.match("Introduction / extension of measures")
cummeasure["Value"]=cummeasure["Value"].astype(int)
cummeasure["Value"]=cummeasure["Value"]*2-1
cummeasure = cummeasure.groupby('DATE_IMPLEMENTED').Value.sum()
cummeasure = cummeasure.groupby(cummeasure.index.time).cumsum().reset_index()
cummeasure.set_index('DATE_IMPLEMENTED', inplace=True)
cummeasure.plot(figsize=(15,5), linewidth=5, fontsize=20)
plt.xlabel('Month', fontsize=20)
plt.ylabel('Number of measures', fontsize=15)
plt.title("Trend of measures implemented overtime around the world",fontsize=20)

Massively Multiplayer, despite the lack of human contact over the pandemic, did not seem to increase much at all. This could be due to the fact Massively Multiplayer requires a lot of time investment into the game, allowing people to constantly socialise with others, which may not be what people have wanted during the pandemic.

Instead, the data suggests that people were more stress than they were isolated and just needed a way to relieve it.
